</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF85FFF9FF591BAE8787B087" blockId="18.[160,1155,419,652]" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">
This fiddler crab was very common. We found it in on St. Thomas from the lowest reaches of Neltjeberg Ghut, well inside the tree line, as much as 100 metres from the sea in ghuts and artificial ditches. We also found it on St. Thomas in estuarine and brackish conditions at Magens Beach, Mandahl Bay, Abi Beach, Mangrove Lagoon, and a ditch in Crown Bay, often in freshwater. We also found large numbers of this species in the saline ponds on 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF85FFF9FE8F185C84CCB061" box="[278,408,593,618]" name="Saba Island" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">Saba Island</collectingCountry>
(new record). 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF85FFF9FDD8185C878DB061" author="Beatty HA" box="[577,729,593,618]" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" pagination="261 - 268" refId="ref22509" refString="Beatty HA. 1968. A checklist of Crustacea of St. Croix, Virgin Islands. J Agric Univ Puerto Rico. 52: 261 - 268. doi: 10.46429 / jaupr. v 52 i 3.11514." type="journal article" year="1968">Beatty (1968)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF85FFF9FD7F185C8154B061" author="Chase FA &amp; Hobbs HH" box="[742,1024,593,618]" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" pagination="1 - 245" refId="ref23476" refString="Chase FA, Hobbs HH. 1969. The freshwater and terrestrial decapod crustaceans of the West Indies, with special reference to Dominica. U S Natl Mus Bull. 292: 1 - 245. doi: 10.5479 / si. 03629236.292.1." type="journal article" year="1969">Chase and Hobbs (1969)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF85FFF9FBDB185C85B2B087" author="Crane J" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" refId="ref23747" refString="Crane J. 1975. Fiddler crabs of the world, Ocypodidae: genus Uca. New Jersey (USA): Princeton University Press; p. 736." type="journal volume" year="1975">Crane (1975)</bibRefCitation>
give records from St. Thomas and St. Croix.
</paragraph>
